**What changed** (`backend/src/main/java/com/tepeu/service/WorkspacePathResolver.java:81-85`):

After normalizing the resolved path, added a `startsWith(basePath)` boundary check. If the normalized result escapes the base directory, returns `null` instead of the out-of-bounds path.

```java
if (!resolved.startsWith(basePath.normalize())) {
    return null;
}
```

This matches the null-return contract that `FileTools.java` (and `FileController.java`) already check for, and passes all 5 `resolveSafely_*` tests including the traversal-rejection cases.
